722415f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 135th Street (East)
722415f-a.text:
Park Avenue a .d East 135th Street at the Harlem
River, showing a fire boat station ''Engine 47'' at that
location. The photographer is viewing southwestward
(to show the 4 story Crane Co. Warehouse in the back-
ground. This occupies the entire westerly side of Park
Avenue from 134th to 135th Streets. View No. 2 is in
the opposite directlon, looking toward the Bronx shore
of the Harlem River.
View 1: Fall 1935
View 2: March 6, 1936
P. L. Sperr
